                                                                      SECTION 3
 
 
                                                      INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
       ________________________________       COMMON INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
 
 
       Copy the patches from the tape into the .SUPPORT account.  Merge your
       TIGR file into the patch file using PMERGE.X (see PMERGE_HELP.X).  After
       the patch file is ready, $XDEF_MINI.SUPPORT is used to rebuild the first
       volume of the P.O. tape set which can then be used with existing volume
       2 (and possibly 3) to reboot the system.  Boots of this type, for the
       purpose of installing new patches, are done with 'S' to NEW FILE SYSTEM.
 
 
 
       __________________________________       INSTALLATION OF SOURCE CAP PATCHES
 
 
       Patches to CAP programs are issued through normal patch distribution
       procedures.  TeX macro files cannot be patched in the usual way, so a
       special mechanism has been set up to issue macro changes.
 
       A file containing source patches for CAP (VA:PATCHES) is PMERGEed into
       the !BOOTTIME section of patch decks as part of the procedure to release
       patches to the field.  A JCL file in the SUPPORT account is then used to
       extract VA:PATCHES from the designated patch file and replace the one in
       :SYS.  This JCL is invoked as follows:
 
          $INSTALL_VA:PATCHES.SUPPORT FID$ = 'fid'
 
       where 'fid' is the name.account of the patch file.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
       SRB_PATCHES        Installation of Source CAP Patches                3-1
       
 
 
 
 
 
                                                                               
 
 
